#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:1
msgid "Start Date: 2023-07-24"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:2
msgid ""
"RFC PR: [rust-lang/rfcs#3463](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/3463)"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:4
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:7
msgid ""
"The Rust community has outgrown the current crates.io policies. This RFC "
"proposes a new \"Terms of Use\" policy based on prior work by PyPI, npm and "
"GitHub."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:9
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:12
msgid ""
"Why are we doing this? What use cases does it support? What is the expected "
"outcome?"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:14
msgid ""
"crates.io has a \"[Package Policies](https://crates.io/policies)\" page, "
"which describes the current, organically grown policies. A lot of support "
"requests or questionable uses of crates.io however need explicit decisions "
"from the crates.io team, since many cases are currently not covered by these "
"policies. Additionally, decisions made by the team may be seen as arbitrary "
"without written guidelines."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:16
msgid ""
"The situation around name squatting has lately also reached unsustainable "
"levels, and while [namespaces](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/3243) "
"might help with some parts of the problem we would still need policies for "
"name squatting namespaces then."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:18
msgid ""
"The main motivation for this RFC is to give the crates.io team a fixed set "
"of rules to determine if a project is using crates.io in a reasonable way, "
"or if the user should get a warning and the project potentially be removed. "
"It is mostly codifying the existing practices of the team, except for being "
"more strict regarding name squatting."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:20
msgid "Proposal"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:23
msgid ""
"The following is a proposed new \"Terms of Use\" policy for crates.io, "
"replacing <https://crates.io/policies> and <https://crates.io/data-access>."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:27
msgid "Terms of Use"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:29
msgid ""
"**Short version:** _crates.io is a critical resource for the Rust ecosystem, "
"which hosts a variety of packages from a diverse group of users. That "
"resource is only effective when our users are able to work together as part "
"of a community in good faith. While using crates.io, you must comply with "
"our Acceptable Use Policies, which include some restrictions on content and "
"conduct on crates.io related to user safety, intellectual property, privacy, "
"authenticity, and other limitations. In short, be excellent to each other!_"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:37
msgid "We do not allow content or activity on crates.io that:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:39
msgid ""
"violates the [Code of Conduct](https://www.rust-lang.org/policies/code-of-"
"conduct) of the Rust project"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:41
msgid ""
"is unlawful or promotes unlawful activities, incurring legal liability in "
"the countries the Rust Foundation officially operates in"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:43
msgid "is libelous, defamatory, or fraudulent"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:44
msgid "amounts to phishing or attempted phishing"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:45
msgid ""
"infringes any proprietary right of any party, including patent, trademark, "
"trade secret, copyright, right of publicity, or other right"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:47
msgid ""
"unlawfully shares unauthorized product licensing keys, software for "
"generating unauthorized product licensing keys, or software for bypassing "
"checks for product licensing keys, including extension of a free license "
"beyond its trial period"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:51
msgid ""
"contains malicious code, such as computer viruses, computer worms, rootkits, "
"back doors, or spyware, including content submitted for research purposes "
"(tools designed and documented explicitly to assist in security research are "
"acceptable, but exploits and malware that use the crates.io registry as a "
"deployment or delivery vector are not)"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:56
msgid "uses obfuscation to hide or mask functionality"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:57
msgid ""
"is discriminatory toward, harasses or abuses another individual or group"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:58
msgid ""
"threatens or incites violence toward any individual or group, especially on "
"the basis of who they are"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:60
msgid ""
"is using crates.io as a platform for propagating abuse on other platforms"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:61
msgid ""
"violates the privacy of any third party, such as by posting another person's "
"personal information without consent"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:63
msgid "gratuitously depicts or glorifies violence, including violent images"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:64
msgid ""
"is sexually obscene or relates to sexual exploitation or abuse, including of "
"minors (see \"Sexually Obscene Content\" section below)"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:66
msgid ""
"is off-topic, or interacts with platform features in a way that "
"significantly or repeatedly disrupts the experience of other users"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:68
msgid ""
"exists only to reserve a name for a prolonged period of time (often called "
"\"name squatting\") without having any genuine functionality, purpose, or "
"significant development activity on the corresponding repository"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:71
msgid ""
"is related to buying, selling, or otherwise trading of package names or any "
"other names on crates.io for money or other compensation"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:73
msgid ""
"impersonates any person or entity, including through false association with "
"crates.io, or by fraudulently misrepresenting your identity or site's purpose"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:75
msgid ""
"is related to inauthentic interactions, such as fake accounts and automated "
"inauthentic activity"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:77
msgid ""
"is using our servers for any form of excessive automated bulk activity, to "
"place undue burden on our servers through automated means, or to relay any "
"form of unsolicited advertising or solicitation through our servers, such as "
"get-rich-quick schemes"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:81
msgid ""
"is using our servers for other automated excessive bulk activity or "
"coordinated inauthentic activity, such as"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:83
msgid "spamming"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:84
msgid "cryptocurrency mining"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:85
msgid ""
"is not functionally compatible with the cargo build tool (for example, a "
"\"package\" cannot simply be a PNG or JPEG image, a movie file, or a text "
"document uploaded directly to the registry)"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:88
msgid "is abusing the package index for purposes it was not intended"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:90
msgid ""
"You are responsible for using crates.io in compliance with all applicable "
"laws, regulations, and all of our policies. These policies may be updated "
"from time to time. We will interpret our policies and resolve disputes in "
"favor of protecting users as a whole. The crates.io team reserves the "
"possibility to evaluate each instance on a case-by-case basis."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:96
msgid ""
"For issues such as DMCA violations, or trademark and copyright "
"infringements, the crates.io team will respect the legal decisions of the "
"[Rust Foundation](https://rustfoundation.org/) as the official legal entity "
"providing the crates.io service."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:102
msgid "Package Ownership"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:104
msgid ""
"crates.io has a first-come, first-serve policy on crate names. Upon "
"publishing a package, the publisher will be made owner of the package on "
"crates.io."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:107
msgid ""
"If you want to take over a package, we require you to first try and contact "
"the current owner directly. If the current owner agrees, they can add you as "
"an owner of the crate, and you can then remove them, if necessary. If the "
"current owner is not reachable or has not published any contact information "
"the crates.io team may reach out to help mediate the process of the "
"ownership transfer."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:114
msgid ""
"Crate deletion by their owners is not possible to keep the registry as "
"immutable as possible. If you want to flag your crate as open for "
"transferring ownership to others, you can publish a new version with a "
"message in the README or description communicating to the crates.io support "
"team that you consent to transfer the crate to the first person who asks for "
"it:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:120
msgid ""
"I consent to the transfer of this crate to the first person who asks "
"help@crates.io for it."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:123
msgid ""
"The crates.io team may delete crates from the registry that do not comply "
"with the policies on this document. In larger cases of squatting attacks "
"this may happen without prior notification to the author, but in most cases "
"the team will first give the author the chance to justify the purpose of the "
"crate."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:129
msgid "Data Access"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:131
msgid ""
"If you need access to a large subset of the crates.io database we recommend "
"first looking at the **crates.io [index repository](https://github.com/rust-"
"lang/crates.io-index)**. This repository is updated live whenever new "
"versions are published and contains all the information needed for cargo to "
"run the dependency resolution algorithm."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:136
msgid ""
"In case the index dataset is insufficient for your purposes, we also publish "
"a **database dump** every 24 hours. This includes the majority of data from "
"our database except for sensitive private information. The latest database "
"dump is available at <https://static.crates.io/db-dump.tar.gz> and "
"information on using the content is contained in the tarball. Please note "
"that while we aim to keep the data structure somewhat stable, we can not "
"give any stability guarantees on the exact database table layouts."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:144
msgid ""
"If the index repository and the database dump are insufficient you may also "
"use the crates.io API directly, though it is at the discretion of the crates."
"io to block any excessive usage. We require users of the crates.io API to "
"limit themselves to a maximum of 1 request per second."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:149
msgid ""
"We also require all API users to provide a user-agent header that allows us "
"to uniquely identify your application. This allows us to more accurately "
"monitor any impact your application may have on our service. Providing a "
"user agent that only identifies your HTTP client library (such as "
"`reqwest/0.9.1`) increases the likelihood that we will block your traffic."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:155
msgid ""
"It is recommended, to include contact information in your user-agent header:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:157
msgid "Bad: `User-Agent: reqwest/0.9.1`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:158
msgid "Better: `User-Agent: my_bot`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:159
msgid ""
"Best: `User-Agent: my_bot (my_bot.com/info)` or `User-Agent: my_bot "
"(help@my_bot.com)`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:161
msgid ""
"This allows us to contact you if we would like a change in your "
"application's behavior without having to block your traffic."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:164
msgid ""
"We reserve the right to block traffic from any client that we determine to "
"be in violation of this policy or causing an impact on the integrity of our "
"service."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:168
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:170
msgid ""
"Safety is one of the core principles of Rust, and to that end, we would like "
"to ensure that cargo and crates.io have secure implementations. To learn "
"more about disclosing security vulnerabilities for these tools, please "
"reference the [Rust Security policy](https://www.rust-lang.org/policies/"
"security) for more details."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:176
msgid ""
"Note that this policy only applies to official Rust projects like crates.io "
"and cargo, and not individual crates. The crates.io team and the Security "
"Response working group are not responsible for the disclosure of "
"vulnerabilities to specific crates, and if any issues are found, you should "
"seek guidance from the individual crate owners and their specific policies "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:182
msgid ""
"Thank you for taking the time to responsibly disclose any issues you find."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:185
msgid "Sexually Obscene Content"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:187
msgid ""
"We do not tolerate content associated with sexual exploitation or abuse of "
"another individual, including where minors are concerned. We do not allow "
"sexually themed or suggestive content that serves little or no purpose other "
"than to solicit an erotic or shocking response, particularly where that "
"content is amplified by its placement in profiles or other social contexts."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:193
msgid "This includes:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:195
msgid "Pornographic content"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:196
msgid "Non-consensual intimate imagery"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:197
msgid ""
"Graphic depictions of sexual acts including photographs, video, animation, "
"drawings, computer-generated images, or text-based content"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:200
msgid ""
"We recognize that not all nudity or content related to sexuality is obscene. "
"We may allow visual and/or textual depictions in artistic, educational, "
"historical or journalistic contexts, or as it relates to victim advocacy. In "
"some cases a disclaimer can help communicate the context of the project."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:206
msgid "Violations and Enforcement"
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:208
msgid ""
"crates.io retains full discretion to take action in response to a violation "
"of these policies, including account suspension, account termination, or "
"removal of content."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:212
msgid ""
"We will however not be proactively monitoring the site for these kinds of "
"violations, but instead relying on the community to draw them to our "
"attention."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:215
msgid ""
"While the majority of interactions between individuals in the Rust community "
"falls within our policies, violations of those policies do occur at times. "
"When they do, the crates.io team may need to take enforcement action to "
"address the violations. In all cases, content and account deletion is "
"permanent and there is no basis to reverse these moderation actions taken by "
"the crates.io team. Account suspension may be lifted at the team's "
"discretion however, for example in the case of someone's account being "
"compromised."
msgstr ""

#: src/3463-crates-io-policy-update.md:224
msgid "Credits & License"
msgstr ""

